<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-07-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-07-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="385" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d385">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Philip</persName> to
                                    <persName type="to">M. Malmusi</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tangier</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-07-29"><hi rend="italic">July 29,
                                1903</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p rend="flushleft"><hi rend="smallcaps">Your Excellency</hi>:</p>
                        <p>In pursuance of your letter to the consul-general of June 13 last, I have
                            the honor to inform you that I am in receipt of instructions from my
                            Government authorizing me to enter into a reciprocal agreement with the
                            Government of the Kingdom of Italy and the United States, the agreement
                            to be for the mutual protection of trade-marks registered in Italy and
                            the United States against infringement in Morocco by subjects of the
                            respective nations, on the lines of that now existing between the United
                            States and Great Britain.</p>
                        <p>Accept, Mr. Minister, the assurance of my high consideration.</p>
                        <closer><signed><list>
                                    <item><hi rend="smallcaps">Hoffman Philip</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Consul-General.</hi></item>
                                    <item>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Malmusi</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Minister of Italy.</hi></item>
                                </list></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>